
Overview of verb chaffer

The verb chaffer has 2 senses (no senses from tagged texts)
                                      
1. haggle, higgle, chaffer, huckster -- (wrangle (over a price, terms of an agreement, etc.); "Let's not haggle over a few dollars")
2. chew the fat, shoot the breeze, chat, confabulate, confab, chitchat, chit-chat, chatter, chaffer, natter, gossip, jaw, claver, visit -- (talk socially without exchanging too much information; "the men were sitting in the cafe and shooting the breeze")
